tions from Pushkin, Lermontov, Tyutchev) and have contributed poetry and prose to the New Yorker (several poems) and the Atlantic Monthly (several stories). Most of my time, however, is taken up by scientific papers on butterflies, some of which I have discovered myself during collecting trips in Arizona and Utah.

I am out of town at present but shall have some of my stuff forwarded to you as soon as I get back to Cambridge (a small university town near Boston) where we live.

Keep well, write,